name: img2img with Prompt to Mask
author: MildMisery
description: Use of the clipseg mask node to automatically detect an area of an image from user prompt and produce a mask for it, then apply that mask to the original image and replace it with a new user-inputted generation

prompt.name: prompt
prompt.label: Negative Prompt
prompt.value: <EasyNegative>, young, loli, colored skin, paint, hoodie, (jacket)+++, sleeves

value.model_name: anything KlF8 Anime 2 Vae Ft Mse 840000_klF8Anime2

data.label: Notes
data.notes: For manual seed, remove the connection from the random integer to the primitive and type the seed into the primitive

data.label: Notes
data.notes: To add a lora (such as a specific clothes lora), move the UNet connection from the main model node, and connect it to the Lora, then from the lora, to the Denoise latents node. From the Clip connection from main model to the lora instead of clip skip, then from the lora to skip skip.

data.label: Notes
data.notes:
These prompts are the part of your image you want changed, simple prompts work best, if you want multiple parts changed at once, separate the ideas into the different prompt fields and the node will make a mask for each and then combine them

If the mask is grabbing too much that isn't what you prompted, try raising the subject threshold

data.label: Notes
data.notes:
The control net is making an uncanny model of the image and passing it into the denoise to try and maintain the pose of characters.

If your results are not a similar enough pose, try raising the control weight, if it's too similar, lower it

data.label: Notes
data.notes: Mask edge is here to expand the mask a little bit to grab parts of the image that the mask missed and provide a transition from the original image to the new. Paste is combining the original mask with the edge.

data.label: Notes
data.notes: This node will combine your original image with the produced mask, so you can check how well your prompt worked, and what parts of the image were masked. Check the save to gallery box to get a saved copy of the image with the mask covering it. You can also see this output by selecting the node after invoking the workflow once and checking the output tab below the linear view.
